1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:04,754
[Ahmad] <i>We're going to stage</i>
<i>a public spectacle.</i>

2
00:00:04,838 --> 00:00:07,882
<i>We'll make it look like Datu Rahman</i>
<i>is surrendering to me.</i>

3
00:00:07,966 --> 00:00:10,593
<i>You will challenge Agent Marcus Reyes</i>

4
00:00:10,677 --> 00:00:14,806
<i>to catch and expose</i>
<i>the people who framed you.</i>

5
00:00:14,889 --> 00:00:17,726
[Manuel] <i>We need to execute the plan.</i>

6
00:00:17,809 --> 00:00:20,895
[Dionisio] <i>General Villanueva is convinced</i>
<i>by what Datu Rahman is saying!</i>

7
00:00:20,979 --> 00:00:24,232
<i>That the protector</i>
<i>of the syndicate is inside NLEA!</i>

8
00:00:24,315 --> 00:00:28,570
- [Dionisio] <i>What should we do, General?</i>
- [Manuel] <i>We will give them someone</i>

9
00:00:28,653 --> 00:00:31,197
<i>who can take the fall.</i>

10
00:00:31,281 --> 00:00:33,867
<i>If only you had been competent,</i>

11
00:00:33,950 --> 00:00:36,161
<i>I wouldn't have to go through</i>
<i>all this trouble!</i>

12
00:00:36,244 --> 00:00:38,580
[Lara] <i>Why did you disappear</i>
<i>when the media arrived?</i>

13
00:00:38,663 --> 00:00:40,206
[Jalil] <i>I don't need praise.</i>

14
00:00:40,290 --> 00:00:41,791
[Lara] <i>You're hiding something, Espina.</i>

15
00:00:41,875 --> 00:00:43,960
[man] <i>That's where Datu Rahman</i>
<i>was picked up</i>

16
00:00:44,043 --> 00:00:45,044
<i>by the cop with the glasses.</i>

17
00:00:45,128 --> 00:00:47,630
[Felix] <i>What is Marcus's mother</i>
<i>doing here?</i>

18
00:00:47,714 --> 00:00:50,592
<i>Why does she seem</i>
<i>so important in this place?</i>

19
00:00:51,176 --> 00:00:52,719
[Marcus] <i>There's something</i>
<i>you need to know.</i>

20
00:00:52,802 --> 00:00:55,055
<i>Harold is alive.</i>

21
00:00:55,138 --> 00:00:56,765
<i>He's currently on the island.</i>

22
00:00:56,848 --> 00:00:59,601
[Azuelo] <i>Agent Reyes</i>
<i>returned to Damai Island</i>

23
00:00:59,684 --> 00:01:01,770
<i>to obtain evidence.</i>

24
00:01:01,853 --> 00:01:05,607
<i>Those are the weapons recovered</i>
<i>by Datu Rahman's group.</i>

25
00:01:05,690 --> 00:01:08,401
[Lara] <i>It's confirmed.</i>
<i>Marcus was up to something.</i>

26
00:01:08,485 --> 00:01:09,819
You know what needs to be done.

27
00:01:09,903 --> 00:01:11,237
[in English] Understood, madam.

28
00:01:11,321 --> 00:01:13,239
[Datu Rahman]
<i>You need to go back to the island.</i>

29
00:01:13,323 --> 00:01:15,742
<i>Check on our people.</i>

30
00:01:15,825 --> 00:01:17,410
<i>They suffered a lot.</i>

31
00:01:17,494 --> 00:01:18,787
<i>They need you.</i>

32
00:01:19,454 --> 00:01:21,039
Head to Damai Island.

33
00:01:21,122 --> 00:01:24,834
[Felix] <i>Retrieve all the weapons</i>
<i>buried by Datu Rahman.</i>

34
00:01:25,335 --> 00:01:27,796
Eliminate every trace of life in the area.

35
00:01:27,879 --> 00:01:29,506
I will send my men.

36
00:01:30,423 --> 00:01:34,260
[Felix] <i>This is my revenge</i>
<i>on you, Jalil Abubakar.</i>

37
00:01:37,430 --> 00:01:40,058
[mysterious theme music playing]

38
00:01:53,196 --> 00:01:55,365
- [in English] Okay. You're dismissed.
- [in English] Thank you, sir.

39
00:01:57,450 --> 00:01:58,326
[Azuelo sighs]

40
00:02:02,997 --> 00:02:04,249
[tense music playing]

41
00:02:04,332 --> 00:02:05,208
Emil.

42
00:02:06,626 --> 00:02:08,545
- What are you doing?
- [chair scrapes floor]

43
00:02:09,587 --> 00:02:10,505
Sir?

44
00:02:10,588 --> 00:02:14,634
Did you think I wouldn't hear
about what you've been spouting?

45
00:02:15,218 --> 00:02:21,057
About your suspicions
that there's a mole in NLEA and SID?

46
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:23,810
Nonsense!

47
00:02:24,310 --> 00:02:25,478
‪[dramatic sting]

48
00:02:25,562 --> 00:02:30,191
You're besmirching the very institution

49
00:02:30,275 --> 00:02:33,444
that I worked hard to uphold for years!

50
00:02:38,992 --> 00:02:40,368
- But General--
- Enough!

51
00:02:41,411 --> 00:02:45,123
Has Marcus Reyes gotten to you too?

52
00:02:45,915 --> 00:02:49,419
Are you really going to side
with Datu Rahman

53
00:02:49,502 --> 00:02:51,337
over your own men?

54
00:02:51,421 --> 00:02:56,384
Even Villanueva has started
his own investigation!

55
00:02:56,467 --> 00:02:57,385
Seriously?!

56
00:02:57,886 --> 00:03:02,891
[scoffs] I never expected him to believe

57
00:03:02,974 --> 00:03:06,436
your baseless accusations!

58
00:03:09,564 --> 00:03:11,691
[exhales sharply]

59
00:03:11,774 --> 00:03:15,194
[in English] But here we are.

60
00:03:18,156 --> 00:03:19,324
Are you aware…

61
00:03:20,325 --> 00:03:24,871
that even your appointment as general

62
00:03:25,663 --> 00:03:29,417
is on the line because
of the stunts you're pulling?

63
00:03:30,793 --> 00:03:36,007
Did you really think
that they wouldn't consult me

64
00:03:36,090 --> 00:03:40,720
on whether you deserve to be a general?

65
00:03:41,763 --> 00:03:42,889
[scoffs]

66
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:48,186
Do you want me to tell them
that you've gone crazy?

67
00:03:48,895 --> 00:03:52,398
That you're going against…

68
00:03:53,608 --> 00:03:54,734
your own colleagues?

69
00:03:56,611 --> 00:03:57,737
[scoffs]

70
00:03:59,072 --> 00:04:00,073
Sir…

71
00:04:00,990 --> 00:04:04,077
If I know something wrong
is happening around me,

72
00:04:05,036 --> 00:04:06,829
and I choose to remain silent,

73
00:04:08,206 --> 00:04:11,251
that makes me even less deserving
to be a general.

74
00:04:13,461 --> 00:04:15,004
All I want to do

75
00:04:15,088 --> 00:04:18,216
is to root out the bad weeds
in the ranks of NLEA and SID

76
00:04:18,299 --> 00:04:19,592
before I retire.

77
00:04:20,677 --> 00:04:21,803
[in English] That's all, sir.

78
00:04:23,179 --> 00:04:27,600
[in English] You are losing
your damn mind, Emil.

79
00:04:28,351 --> 00:04:29,727
[in English] Are you aware?

80
00:04:30,311 --> 00:04:35,900
Do you know why there is
a semblance of peace and order

81
00:04:35,984 --> 00:04:38,152
here in our country? Hm?

82
00:04:38,987 --> 00:04:41,781
Because of fear.

83
00:04:42,782 --> 00:04:46,577
And the moment that fear disappears…

84
00:04:47,453 --> 00:04:51,249
[exhales] …we will lose
the public's trust!

85
00:04:51,332 --> 00:04:52,875
What do you think will happen to us then?!

86
00:04:52,959 --> 00:04:55,670
[dramatic sting]

87
00:04:56,254 --> 00:04:59,590
[in English] Emil, listen to me.

88
00:05:00,758 --> 00:05:03,136
[in English] And listen to me well.

89
00:05:04,137 --> 00:05:09,183
Think carefully about what you're doing.

90
00:05:09,267 --> 00:05:12,770
[music intensifies]

91
00:05:25,241 --> 00:05:26,075
[music concludes]

92
00:05:26,159 --> 00:05:27,076
Jalil!

93
00:05:38,004 --> 00:05:42,592
[stirring music playing]

94
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:53,978
[Datu Rahman] Get ready!

95
00:05:54,062 --> 00:05:55,438
- You ready?
- Mm!

96
00:05:56,105 --> 00:05:57,065
[huffs]

97
00:05:57,148 --> 00:05:57,899
One!

98
00:05:58,816 --> 00:06:00,568
Two! Three!

99
00:06:00,651 --> 00:06:03,780
[sticks whooshing]

100
00:06:03,863 --> 00:06:10,703
[fire crackling]

101
00:06:13,873 --> 00:06:15,208
[huffing]

102
00:06:17,460 --> 00:06:18,836
[Sali] <i>Keep going, Jalil.</i>

103
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:22,757
<i>A true warrior may bleed and falter,</i>

104
00:06:22,840 --> 00:06:24,425
<i>but he never gives up.</i>

105
00:06:25,551 --> 00:06:27,386
<i>Always remember</i>

106
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:31,182
<i>that we Tausug people</i>
<i>do not seek conflict.</i>

107
00:06:31,265 --> 00:06:33,434
<i>But if necessary,</i>

108
00:06:33,518 --> 00:06:35,853
<i>we never back down from a fight.</i>

109
00:06:38,481 --> 00:06:42,735
<i>This kris, Jalil, is not just a weapon.</i>

110
00:06:43,361 --> 00:06:47,281
<i>It's a symbol of our people and our pride.</i>

111
00:06:47,365 --> 00:06:52,120
<i>It represents the peace</i>
<i>and justice we are fighting for.</i>

112
00:06:52,203 --> 00:06:54,789
<i>The time will come</i>
<i>for you to inherit this.</i>

113
00:06:54,872 --> 00:06:57,834
<i>Use it. Be proud of it.</i>

114
00:06:58,334 --> 00:06:59,710
<i>And remember</i>

115
00:06:59,794 --> 00:07:03,714
<i>that all the warriors</i>
<i>who have used it before you</i>

116
00:07:03,798 --> 00:07:08,719
<i>will be with you in all your fights.</i>

117
00:07:11,639 --> 00:07:12,974
Good job.

118
00:07:13,057 --> 00:07:14,100
Good job, son.

119
00:07:15,601 --> 00:07:19,439
I have taught you everything
I know about fighting.

120
00:07:21,315 --> 00:07:25,528
Now, you are ready to protect our island.

121
00:07:29,824 --> 00:07:35,872
[dramatic sting]

122
00:07:41,586 --> 00:07:43,796
[man] Take Grandpa Sali's kris.

123
00:07:44,297 --> 00:07:45,423
It's for you.

124
00:07:50,678 --> 00:07:53,890
- [rapid gunfire]
- [people clamoring]

125
00:07:55,683 --> 00:07:57,393
- [screams]
- Take cover!

126
00:07:57,477 --> 00:08:04,400
[people screaming]

127
00:08:06,277 --> 00:08:11,365
- [fire crackling]
- [dramatic music playing]

128
00:08:11,449 --> 00:08:12,950
[in Arabic] <i>God is great!</i>

129
00:08:14,619 --> 00:08:16,162
[grunting and groaning]

130
00:08:17,788 --> 00:08:22,043
I made sure to retrieve it
after Task Force Alpha left.

131
00:08:22,126 --> 00:08:24,962
I cleaned and kept it safe

132
00:08:25,046 --> 00:08:27,965
because I knew the day would come
when you'd need it again.

133
00:08:31,636 --> 00:08:32,637
No…

134
00:08:33,137 --> 00:08:34,347
No.

135
00:08:34,430 --> 00:08:36,849
That's your grandfather's.
You should have it.

136
00:08:37,433 --> 00:08:40,228
You were his finest student.

137
00:08:40,311 --> 00:08:42,855
You're also the one who saved our island.

138
00:08:42,939 --> 00:08:45,149
It's only right
that you inherit this kris.

139
00:08:45,816 --> 00:08:47,360
And I know that Grandpa

140
00:08:47,443 --> 00:08:51,405
would have wanted no one else
to have it but you.

141
00:08:52,740 --> 00:08:55,701
Because he knew that
you would use it for good.

142
00:08:56,202 --> 00:09:02,416
[music intensifying]

143
00:09:05,211 --> 00:09:09,590
- [grunting]
- [gunshots]

144
00:09:09,674 --> 00:09:10,841
[gunshots]

145
00:09:33,823 --> 00:09:38,286
[dramatic ethereal music playing]

146
00:09:43,583 --> 00:09:44,667
[in Tausug] Thank you.

147
00:09:51,632 --> 00:09:52,717
[in Tausug] Thank you.

148
00:10:06,981 --> 00:10:11,819
Sheikh Datu Abdurahman Abubakar.

149
00:10:13,487 --> 00:10:16,991
I know you're being accused,

150
00:10:17,074 --> 00:10:20,119
just like what happened to other Muslims.

151
00:10:21,495 --> 00:10:25,458
But I also know that
you're hiding something.

152
00:10:28,336 --> 00:10:30,087
What are you, really?

153
00:10:30,171 --> 00:10:34,634
[tense music playing]

154
00:10:34,717 --> 00:10:36,761
What are you hiding?

155
00:10:39,513 --> 00:10:40,598
Sheikh…

156
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:45,728
unidentified men abducted you.

157
00:10:45,811 --> 00:10:47,396
They were armed.

158
00:10:47,897 --> 00:10:49,231
To this day,

159
00:10:49,315 --> 00:10:51,108
they're still looking for you.

160
00:10:51,776 --> 00:10:56,447
You must know something,
or you're valuable to them.

161
00:10:56,530 --> 00:10:57,782
Otherwise,

162
00:10:59,283 --> 00:11:00,284
you would've been killed a long time ago.

163
00:11:00,368 --> 00:11:03,162
[dramatic sting]

164
00:11:04,038 --> 00:11:05,164
- Brother…
- [inhales]

165
00:11:06,165 --> 00:11:11,504
the safety of our country
lies in your hands.

166
00:11:11,587 --> 00:11:15,049
As well as your safety

167
00:11:15,549 --> 00:11:17,968
and the safety of your family
and children.

168
00:11:18,052 --> 00:11:19,762
Tell me.

169
00:11:20,596 --> 00:11:21,555
What secret are you hiding?

170
00:11:21,639 --> 00:11:26,936
[dramatic sting]

171
00:11:27,853 --> 00:11:30,356
[breathes heavily]

172
00:11:33,484 --> 00:11:36,237
I'm not sure, Secretary,

173
00:11:37,154 --> 00:11:39,657
if it has anything to do with my past.

174
00:11:39,740 --> 00:11:41,033
Past?

175
00:11:42,535 --> 00:11:43,619
What past?

176
00:11:43,702 --> 00:11:49,917
[dramatic sting]

177
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:54,296
[breathing heavily]

178
00:11:59,760 --> 00:12:01,220
Secretary Mustapha.

179
00:12:03,180 --> 00:12:07,685
Please don't tell my children
what I'm about to tell you.

180
00:12:09,103 --> 00:12:12,064
I've kept it a secret from them
for a long time.

181
00:12:14,191 --> 00:12:16,235
I'm only telling you this.

182
00:12:16,318 --> 00:12:18,028
[exhales, in Arabic] God willing.

183
00:12:18,112 --> 00:12:22,199
[tense music continues]

184
00:12:22,283 --> 00:12:23,909
My real name is…

185
00:12:25,661 --> 00:12:26,871
Hasan Wadi.

186
00:12:28,038 --> 00:12:32,877
I used to work
for Colonel Napoleon Marcelino.

187
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:36,464
He was the late colonel
who ran a syndicate

188
00:12:36,547 --> 00:12:39,842
selling illegal weapons.

189
00:12:39,925 --> 00:12:42,678
[music turns mysterious]

190
00:12:42,761 --> 00:12:45,139
But it turned out
that wasn't his only goal.

191
00:12:45,723 --> 00:12:48,309
He had a much deeper purpose.

192
00:12:49,226 --> 00:12:51,520
He stirred up chaos

193
00:12:53,230 --> 00:12:57,109
because he wanted to weaken
and ultimately overthrow the government.

194
00:12:58,152 --> 00:13:02,907
So that in the end, the power
would fall into his hands.

195
00:13:05,701 --> 00:13:07,286
But I learned the truth too late.

196
00:13:08,287 --> 00:13:11,040
Many innocent lives have been lost.

197
00:13:11,832 --> 00:13:13,584
He was willing to kill anyone…

198
00:13:14,418 --> 00:13:15,669
whether young or old,

199
00:13:16,795 --> 00:13:18,839
just to carry out his plan.

200
00:13:19,757 --> 00:13:23,636
[tense music playing]

201
00:13:29,725 --> 00:13:31,477
- [explosion]
- [people screaming]

202
00:13:31,560 --> 00:13:34,980
[Rahman] <i>Like what happened</i>
<i>during a medical mission in Mindanao.</i>

203
00:13:35,648 --> 00:13:38,025
<i>He was the one who stirred up chaos,</i>

204
00:13:38,108 --> 00:13:41,403
<i>but the Muslim rebels were blamed for it.</i>

205
00:13:41,487 --> 00:13:43,989
<i>I tried to stop him, but there</i>
<i>was nothing I could do.</i>

206
00:13:44,073 --> 00:13:46,867
[young Lara] <i>Mommy! Daddy!</i>

207
00:13:48,327 --> 00:13:49,620
[Datu Rahman] <i>That's when I realized</i>

208
00:13:49,703 --> 00:13:51,872
- What did you do?!
- <i>that despite his claim</i>

209
00:13:52,456 --> 00:13:56,085
<i>of wanting a peaceful world,</i>

210
00:13:56,168 --> 00:14:00,464
<i>he was willing to sacrifice</i>
<i>countless innocent lives.</i>

211
00:14:00,548 --> 00:14:05,302
[grim music playing]

212
00:14:05,386 --> 00:14:07,721
<i>He made me believe that his plan</i>

213
00:14:07,805 --> 00:14:12,226
<i>was the path to a peaceful</i>
<i>and safe nation,</i>

214
00:14:12,309 --> 00:14:15,813
<i>but it was all a lie!</i>

215
00:14:15,896 --> 00:14:18,148
<i>We weren't revolutionaries.</i>

216
00:14:18,232 --> 00:14:21,068
We were nothing but hardened criminals!

217
00:14:21,151 --> 00:14:25,739
[grim music continues]

218
00:14:25,823 --> 00:14:27,825
I wanted to leave the syndicate back then,

219
00:14:29,159 --> 00:14:31,203
but I knew the colonel wouldn't allow it.

220
00:14:33,163 --> 00:14:36,292
Because he considered me
his right-hand man.

221
00:14:38,752 --> 00:14:42,256
Leaving him would be a grave betrayal.

222
00:14:43,257 --> 00:14:44,592
I was scared too.

223
00:14:44,675 --> 00:14:46,176
Because I knew…

224
00:14:46,260 --> 00:14:48,137
I knew he was going to kill me.

225
00:14:48,220 --> 00:14:50,222
[music intensifies]

226
00:14:50,306 --> 00:14:53,350
Eventually, I got my chance.

227
00:14:57,980 --> 00:14:58,898
- Hasan!
- [gasps]

228
00:15:00,149 --> 00:15:01,901
Look, my family's on this ship.

229
00:15:01,984 --> 00:15:04,236
Are you sure there are bombs here?

230
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:05,738
The police have gotten wind

231
00:15:05,821 --> 00:15:07,489
that there's a hidden shipment
of weapons here.

232
00:15:07,573 --> 00:15:10,200
They're just waiting for the ship
to dock at the pier.

233
00:15:10,284 --> 00:15:12,119
The major planted a bomb here

234
00:15:12,202 --> 00:15:14,163
to erase all the evidence
that could point to him.

235
00:15:14,246 --> 00:15:16,540
That bastard! [grunts]

236
00:15:16,624 --> 00:15:18,667
So many innocent people will die!

237
00:15:18,751 --> 00:15:21,337
- Including my family!
- We need to find the bomb,

238
00:15:22,129 --> 00:15:24,423
so we can defuse it
and save all the people here!

239
00:15:24,506 --> 00:15:25,883
Hasan, help me!

240
00:15:25,966 --> 00:15:28,177
- [dramatic sting]
- Help me save them!

241
00:15:28,260 --> 00:15:30,471
This is the last thing I can do for them.

242
00:15:30,554 --> 00:15:31,597
Please.

243
00:15:32,890 --> 00:15:33,933
[Victor breathing laboriously]

244
00:15:34,016 --> 00:15:36,393
[fire alarm ringing]

245
00:15:37,561 --> 00:15:38,479
Victor!

246
00:15:40,522 --> 00:15:41,857
Victor!

247
00:15:43,108 --> 00:15:44,360
- Victor!
- Hasan…

248
00:15:44,443 --> 00:15:46,070
[gasping]

249
00:15:46,153 --> 00:15:47,655
My children…

250
00:15:49,490 --> 00:15:52,952
P-Please save them… Save them…

251
00:15:53,035 --> 00:15:55,829
[gasping]

252
00:15:55,913 --> 00:15:57,039
[Hasan] Victor!

253
00:15:57,665 --> 00:15:59,375
Victor!

254
00:16:00,167 --> 00:16:02,169
Victor!

255
00:16:02,252 --> 00:16:07,257
[grim music playing]

256
00:16:07,341 --> 00:16:09,134
[Hasan, in Tausug] Help! Help!

257
00:16:09,218 --> 00:16:11,845
- [woman] <i>What happened?</i>
- [Hasan] <i>Help!</i>

258
00:16:18,727 --> 00:16:22,106
I moved to Damai Island.

259
00:16:24,274 --> 00:16:26,318
I changed my name,

260
00:16:26,402 --> 00:16:28,112
started a family,

261
00:16:28,195 --> 00:16:30,572
and built a new life,

262
00:16:31,156 --> 00:16:37,496
while the syndicate continued
spreading illegal firearms in Mindanao.

263
00:16:40,165 --> 00:16:44,044
Over time, they came closer
and closer to us.

264
00:16:45,504 --> 00:16:47,339
For the past five years,

265
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:51,885
they had been dropping weapons
into the sea near our island.

266
00:16:51,969 --> 00:16:53,012
Mm-hmm.

267
00:16:54,138 --> 00:16:54,972
‪[sighs]

268
00:16:55,055 --> 00:16:56,181
That's when I realized…

269
00:16:57,641 --> 00:17:01,228
I had to protect
the people who took me in.

270
00:17:01,311 --> 00:17:03,605
[pensive music playing]

271
00:17:03,689 --> 00:17:05,733
So, in my own small way,

272
00:17:06,775 --> 00:17:07,776
I fought back.

273
00:17:09,278 --> 00:17:10,612
Only now do I realize

274
00:17:10,696 --> 00:17:14,033
it was the same syndicate I once escaped.

275
00:17:15,034 --> 00:17:19,204
But this time, it's bigger,
more ruthless, stronger,

276
00:17:19,288 --> 00:17:20,789
and more powerful.

277
00:17:20,873 --> 00:17:23,417
[stirring music playing]

278
00:17:23,500 --> 00:17:24,835
Because of me…

279
00:17:27,087 --> 00:17:29,506
they found out where I was.

280
00:17:32,426 --> 00:17:36,180
The people who took me in
were dragged into it.

281
00:17:36,263 --> 00:17:38,682
Including my fellow townspeople.

282
00:17:39,266 --> 00:17:40,851
A lot of people died!

283
00:17:40,934 --> 00:17:42,478
Because of me!

284
00:17:42,561 --> 00:17:44,146
[sniffles]

285
00:17:45,189 --> 00:17:46,648
It's my fault.

286
00:17:48,358 --> 00:17:50,152
It's my fault it happened.

287
00:17:51,528 --> 00:17:54,323
They all died because of me.

288
00:17:58,786 --> 00:17:59,661
They're after you.

289
00:18:02,289 --> 00:18:03,999
That's the only reason I see.

290
00:18:05,042 --> 00:18:07,669
They're doing this just to punish me.

291
00:18:09,296 --> 00:18:14,176
But Datu, Colonel Marcelino's
been dead for ages.

292
00:18:15,761 --> 00:18:17,137
[inhales sharply] Yeah.

293
00:18:17,888 --> 00:18:19,264
But I can feel…

294
00:18:22,017 --> 00:18:24,895
the system he built…

295
00:18:25,938 --> 00:18:29,942
is still moving, even without him.

296
00:18:31,401 --> 00:18:34,363
The syndicate's still active?

297
00:18:36,490 --> 00:18:41,620
[pensive music playing]

298
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:48,919
Who's keeping his plans going?

299
00:18:51,171 --> 00:18:56,510
[music intensifies]

300
00:18:58,428 --> 00:19:01,223
The plan we worked on so long

301
00:19:01,306 --> 00:19:04,226
is finally coming together, Dante.

302
00:19:04,309 --> 00:19:05,352
[chuckles]

303
00:19:06,186 --> 00:19:07,062
[inhales softly]

304
00:19:07,146 --> 00:19:08,897
I really hope…

305
00:19:10,190 --> 00:19:14,319
you'll stand with me till the end.

306
00:19:14,403 --> 00:19:17,614
[dark music playing]

307
00:19:17,698 --> 00:19:19,283
Of course, Manuel.

308
00:19:22,161 --> 00:19:23,495
You can always count on me.

309
00:19:23,579 --> 00:19:25,080
[chuckles softly]

310
00:19:26,039 --> 00:19:27,166
[in English] Good.

311
00:19:27,249 --> 00:19:28,083
‪[dramatic sting]

312
00:19:28,750 --> 00:19:30,002
[Manuel, in English] Good.

313
00:19:32,546 --> 00:19:37,509
[music intensifies]

314
00:19:46,393 --> 00:19:47,352
[CJ laughs]

315
00:19:47,436 --> 00:19:50,022
- [Miggy] That's solid, bro!
- [Jack] So good, bro.

316
00:19:50,105 --> 00:19:51,899
[Jack] Told ya it was good. Crazy good.

317
00:19:51,982 --> 00:19:53,609
[Miggy] Wait till you see this.

318
00:19:53,692 --> 00:19:55,736
- [students laughing] Oh!
- [Miggy] That's sick, bro!

319
00:19:55,819 --> 00:19:58,447
[CJ laughs, claps] So awesome!

320
00:19:58,530 --> 00:20:03,744
[suspenseful music playing]

321
00:20:20,969 --> 00:20:22,679
- [CJ] Hey, bro, let's head out.
- [Jack] Come on.

322
00:20:22,763 --> 00:20:25,891
- [CJ] Wait, someone's gonna…
- [Jack] Right, I almost forgot.

323
00:20:25,974 --> 00:20:28,185
[Miggy] Alright, cut it out, you two.

324
00:20:28,268 --> 00:20:29,561
[kid] Come on!

325
00:20:29,645 --> 00:20:31,563
- [Miggy] You wanna skip class?
- [Jack] Let's just go already.

326
00:20:31,647 --> 00:20:32,731
[CJ] Give me like ten minutes, okay?

327
00:20:32,814 --> 00:20:34,900
- Just gotta finish this.
- It's so freaking hot out.

328
00:20:34,983 --> 00:20:36,944
- [Miggy] There's nothing to do.
- [CJ] We aced that test, right?

329
00:20:37,027 --> 00:20:38,237
[Miggy] Alright then, let's move! Come on.

330
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:41,114
- [Jack] What are we gonna do?
- [Miggy] Just hang out.

331
00:20:41,198 --> 00:20:42,449
Sounds good to me, bro.

332
00:20:44,284 --> 00:20:45,535
Psst! There he is!

333
00:20:45,619 --> 00:20:49,081
There's that weirdo again! [laughing]

334
00:20:49,164 --> 00:20:51,541
- Ugh, he's such a total dork.
- Hey.

335
00:20:51,625 --> 00:20:54,127
[suspenseful music continues]

336
00:20:54,211 --> 00:20:55,504
What'd I tell you, huh?

337
00:20:55,587 --> 00:20:59,299
Didn't I say we never
wanna see your face?!

338
00:21:00,342 --> 00:21:03,262
Huh?! What's with that look?

339
00:21:03,345 --> 00:21:04,930
You think you're better
than us or something?

340
00:21:05,013 --> 00:21:06,848
- You wanna fight or what?
- [Gabriel grunts]

341
00:21:07,641 --> 00:21:08,517
He's such a wimp anyway!

342
00:21:10,310 --> 00:21:13,230
Well?! You gonna stand up for yourself?!

343
00:21:17,317 --> 00:21:20,570
Why are you wearing a jacket?!
It's scorching!

344
00:21:20,654 --> 00:21:22,948
You trying to show off
or something? Take it off!

345
00:21:23,031 --> 00:21:24,992
- I said take it off right now!
- CJ, that's enough!

346
00:21:25,075 --> 00:21:26,952
- [Kyle] Stop it!
- [screams]

347
00:21:27,035 --> 00:21:30,414
[suspensefu; music playing]

348
00:21:30,497 --> 00:21:32,457
[panicked breathing]

349
00:21:32,541 --> 00:21:34,042
- [Miggy] Whoa.
- What is that thing?

350
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:36,461
- Is that a toy gun?
- [laughter]

351
00:21:36,545 --> 00:21:39,548
You messing with us right now?
[mocking laughter]

352
00:21:39,631 --> 00:21:42,217
[Jack] You think we're scared
of that garbage?! Loser!

353
00:21:42,301 --> 00:21:43,593
[CJ] Oh, so you think
you can scare us now?!

354
00:21:44,094 --> 00:21:45,637
You think you're tough
enough to mess with us?!

355
00:21:45,721 --> 00:21:48,307
- Ah! [gunshots]
- [trash can thuds]

356
00:21:48,390 --> 00:21:51,893
[suspenseful music playing]

357
00:21:51,977 --> 00:21:53,770
- [students screaming]
- [CJ grunts]

358
00:21:53,854 --> 00:21:55,272
- [students screaming]
- [CJ grunts]

359
00:21:57,649 --> 00:22:00,193
- [alarm bell ringing]
- [screaming continues]

360
00:22:00,277 --> 00:22:03,113
[sobbing softly, mumbles]

361
00:22:07,617 --> 00:22:09,453
[woman] What is going on out there?!

362
00:22:09,536 --> 00:22:10,912
[CJ] Bro! Help me!

363
00:22:10,996 --> 00:22:16,084
- [alarm bell ringing]
- [screaming]

364
00:22:16,168 --> 00:22:17,586
[breath quivers]

365
00:22:17,669 --> 00:22:18,879
[CJ] Bro!

366
00:22:18,962 --> 00:22:22,591
[CJ whimpers]

367
00:22:22,674 --> 00:22:23,884
[CJ] Bro! Help!

368
00:22:23,967 --> 00:22:27,054
- [alarm bell ringing]
- [grunts, coughs]

369
00:22:29,181 --> 00:22:30,557
[CJ groans, sobs]

370
00:22:32,100 --> 00:22:35,562
[CJ sobbing]

371
00:22:44,905 --> 00:22:50,285
[students screaming]

372
00:23:14,392 --> 00:23:17,104
[grunts softly]

373
00:23:17,187 --> 00:23:18,647
[suspenseful music playing]

374
00:23:18,730 --> 00:23:21,024
Sir?

375
00:23:21,108 --> 00:23:22,901
Sir, we just got an alert.

376
00:23:22,984 --> 00:23:25,695
There's an active shooting in a school,
East Valley Montessori.

377
00:23:27,364 --> 00:23:28,573
East Valley?!

378
00:23:28,657 --> 00:23:31,785
- [alarm bell ringing]
- [suspenseful music playing]

379
00:23:31,868 --> 00:23:33,120
[breathes shakily]

380
00:23:34,579 --> 00:23:36,873
[sobs softly]

381
00:23:39,417 --> 00:23:40,752
[panicked breathing]

382
00:23:40,836 --> 00:23:47,259
[music intesifies, majestic choir rises]

383
00:23:48,093 --> 00:23:49,136
[phone buzzing]

384
00:23:50,053 --> 00:23:52,722
Kyle. Son.

385
00:23:52,806 --> 00:23:54,891
[breathing heavily] Dad.

386
00:23:55,851 --> 00:23:57,602
How are you? Where are you?

387
00:24:00,272 --> 00:24:02,065
I came face-to-face
with a bloody nightmare.

388
00:24:02,149 --> 00:24:03,066
[gasping]

389
00:24:04,151 --> 00:24:07,028
- [dramatic sting]
- [unnerving music playing]

390
00:24:07,112 --> 00:24:09,990
- I got a baseball bat with me.
- [Azuelo, in English] <i>Good.</i>

391
00:24:10,073 --> 00:24:12,993
[in English] You stay put, okay?

392
00:24:14,661 --> 00:24:18,456
[suspenseful music playing]

393
00:24:18,540 --> 00:24:22,419
- [people screaming]
- [man grunts]

394
00:24:23,003 --> 00:24:24,004
Kyle?

395
00:24:25,088 --> 00:24:28,967
[Kyle sobbing] Dad, I'm so scared.

396
00:24:30,510 --> 00:24:35,473
- [screaming]
- [unnerving music playing]

397
00:24:35,557 --> 00:24:37,309
[breath hitches] Dad, please remember…

398
00:24:38,935 --> 00:24:43,023
I love you and Mommy so, so much…

399
00:24:43,690 --> 00:24:47,527
[unnerving music playing]

400
00:24:47,611 --> 00:24:52,449
And my siblings too…
I love every single one of you.

401
00:24:52,949 --> 00:24:53,867
[Azuelo] <i>Kyle, listen.</i>

402
00:24:53,950 --> 00:24:58,580
We're coming to get you
and everyone there.

403
00:24:59,331 --> 00:25:02,334
[Azuelo] <i>Okay? We won't let</i>
<i>anything happen to you.</i>

404
00:25:02,417 --> 00:25:07,839
[unnerving music playing]

405
00:25:07,923 --> 00:25:09,633
Put your phone on silent right now.

406
00:25:09,716 --> 00:25:13,136
And don't make a single sound.

407
00:25:13,220 --> 00:25:14,429
[Azuelo] <i>Okay?</i>

408
00:25:14,512 --> 00:25:15,972
Yes, Dad. [sniffles]

409
00:25:17,724 --> 00:25:18,642
- Agent Angeles.
- Sir.

410
00:25:18,725 --> 00:25:21,770
Call every member of Task Force Alpha.

411
00:25:21,853 --> 00:25:26,107
We're heading straight
to East Valley Montessori.

412
00:25:26,191 --> 00:25:28,610
My son needs me. Now!

413
00:25:28,693 --> 00:25:29,945
[in English] On it, sir.

414
00:25:30,028 --> 00:25:33,448
[dramatic music playing]

415
00:25:54,511 --> 00:25:55,845
[Jalil] I'll teach you this

416
00:25:55,929 --> 00:25:59,099
so you know exactly
how to defend yourselves.

417
00:25:59,182 --> 00:26:03,186
[Jalil] <i>Make sure you're ready to kill</i>
<i>if you point this at anyone.</i>

418
00:26:03,270 --> 00:26:03,812
[man] Jalil!

419
00:26:03,895 --> 00:26:05,522
[man] <i>Armed men are coming!</i>

420
00:26:05,605 --> 00:26:07,274
[Jalil] Hurry! Everyone hide right now!

421
00:26:08,608 --> 00:26:11,194
- [woman] <i>Erick's still inside!</i>
- [sobbing]

422
00:26:11,278 --> 00:26:13,822
- [Marcus] <i>It's still too unstable…</i>
- [in English] What's taking you so long?!

423
00:26:13,905 --> 00:26:16,658
Trust us, we will save your son.

424
00:26:16,741 --> 00:26:19,619
[Marcus] <i>Our goal for this mission</i>
<i>is zero casualties.</i>

425
00:26:19,703 --> 00:26:20,578
[in English] <i>Understood?</i>

426
00:26:20,662 --> 00:26:21,955
[CJ] <i>Help!</i>

427
00:26:22,038 --> 00:26:24,124
[Felix] You loved being a big tough bully,

428
00:26:24,207 --> 00:26:25,625
but look at you crying now.

429
00:26:25,709 --> 00:26:27,961
- CJ!
- [CJ] <i>Wait for me!</i>

430
00:26:28,044 --> 00:26:29,838
[CJ] <i>Wait up!</i>

431
00:26:29,921 --> 00:26:32,215
- This is all your fault!
- N-No…

432
00:26:32,299 --> 00:26:34,926
[sobbing] You made
my whole life miserable.

433
00:26:36,469 --> 00:26:38,888
[Azuelo] <i>Save my son, Reyes.</i>

434
00:26:38,972 --> 00:26:40,807
<i>Bring Kyle back to me, please.</i>

435
00:26:40,890 --> 00:26:42,684
[man] <i>I understand how you feel!</i>

436
00:26:42,767 --> 00:26:45,687
- [man] <i>Just surrender, Gab, please!</i>
- [Gabriel] <i>No way!</i>

437
00:26:45,770 --> 00:26:47,147
[gunshots]

438
00:26:47,230 --> 00:26:48,648
[tense music playing]
